value: Gulliver’s Travels into several remote nations of the world

In several travels Lemuel Gulliver visits remote and strange parts of the world, like the meanwhile proverbial Lilliput. Swift created with this book, seven years after Defoe’s Robinson Crusoe, a predecessor for many of today’s literature categories.
